tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Laboratory results are largely within normal limits. Hemoglobin A1c is at the upper limit, suggesting prediabetes. Chloride is mildly elevated and total CO₂ is slightly low, which may indicate a mild metabolic acidosis or compensation; clinical correlation is advised. Renal function and electrolytes are otherwise normal. Recommend monitoring glucose control and further evaluation if symptoms or risk factors for acid-base disturbances are present.
